 Super Eagles’ defender Ola Aina Playing for the super eagles is a rare privilege that doesn’t come often. playing for the super eagles comes with a lot of wealth as well. Sponsors, businesspeople, and football fans have invested millions of dollars to make football a profitable business. From their humble beginnings at the grassroots level, Nigerian footballers are doing their thing, analyzing how their money spins. 10. Ola Aina – Net Worth (3.1 Billion) Ola Aina is famous for becoming the first Nigerian to win the prestigious Premier League goal of the month in November 2020 with a spectacular effort from outside the box in Fulham’s 2-0 win over West Bromwich Albion. He has an estimated net worth of 3.1 Billion (£6,327,360). Nigeria’s forward Moses Simon poses with the man of the match trophy afetr the Group D Africa Cup of Nations (CAN) 2021 football match between Nigeria and Sudan at Stade Roumde Adjia in Garoua on January 15, 2022. (Photo by Daniel BELOUMOU OLOMO / AFP) 9. Moses Simon, a winger for Nantes FC in Ligue 1, has a net worth of 3.4 billion yen. After defeating Nice in the finals of the 2021/22 season, the dazzling forward, who is 26 years old, helped his team win their fourth French cup title.
Moses is one of the Super Eagles players with the highest net worth and earns approximately £29,000 per week playing for his French team.
Moses Simon’s current contract ends in June 2024, and his estimated net worth is around 3.405 billion (£6,961,240). Despite the fact that he has been the subject of numerous rumors about a summer move away from France. Nigeria’s forward Henry Onyekuru attends a training session in Garoua on January 22, 2022, on the eve of the Africa Cup of Nations (CAN) football match between Nigeria and Tunisia. (Photo by Daniel Beloumou Olomo / AFP) 8. Henry Onyekuru has a net worth of 4.78 billion yen. Currently, on loan from Olympiacos in Greece, Henry Onyekuru plays for Adana Demirspor in Turkey.
The forward, who was born in Lagos, has played for a number of European teams, including Galatasaray, Everton, and AS Monaco, among others.
With an estimated net worth of approximately 4.787 billion naira (£9,796,800), the attacker, who is 25 years old, is one of the highest-paid Nigerian players. ADEMOLA LOOKMAN PHOTO:AFP 7. Ademola Lookman is the seventh richest Super Eagles player by net worth, with a net worth of 6.26 billion yen. Lookman plays for RB Leipzig. He earns approximately £2,704,000 per year, making him one of the Super Eagles stars with the highest earnings. After switching allegiance from England, the 24-year-old attacker made his Super Eagles debut this year. He is one of the future stars of the Nigerian national team. Lookman has an estimated net worth of about 6.267 billion yen (12,718,160 pounds) and spent last season on loan at Leicester City. 6. Napoli talisman Victor Osimhen is the second-highest-paid Nigerian footballer in the world. His net worth is 6.66 billion naira. The forward, who is currently 23 years old, has established himself as one of the most deadly strikers in the Italian league and recently won the Serie A Most Valuable Young Player award.
Osimhen’s annual salary is approximately £5,824,000, and his estimated net worth is 6.662 billion yen (13,598,000 pounds). Because of his lucrative contracts with Lille and Napoli, he has been able to accumulate this much wealth in such a short amount of time.
The striker’s current deal with Napoli ends in 2025, but he is still being talked about leaving Italy this summer, which could almost double his annual salary. Leicester City’s Nigerian striker Kelechi Iheanacho looks to play a pass during the English FA Cup semi-final football match between Leicester City and Southampton at Wembley Stadium in north west London on April 18, 2021. (Photo by Richard Heathcote / POOL / AFP) / NOT FOR MARKETING OR ADVERTISING USE / RESTRICTED TO EDITORIAL USE 5. Kelechi Iheanacho is a footballer who plays for Leicester City FC in the Premier League. His net worth is 11.03 billion yen. The forward, who is 25 years old, is currently the Nigerian player with the most experience playing in the English top division. With his team, he has frequently experienced crucial moments. While playing for Leicester City, Seniorman Kelz, as he is known, earns approximately £4,680,000 per year. He joins the Top 5 richest Super Eagles players with an estimated net worth of around 11.035 billion (£22,360,000). Along with Leicester teammate Wilfred Ndidi and Victor Osimhen, the former Manchester City player also served as a brand ambassador for Multichoice Nigeria.
