4. Alex Iwobi is the fourth richest Super Eagles player on the list, with a net worth of 11.05 billion yen. Iwobi is a star player in the Premier League. Everton FC pays the 26-year-old attacker, who was born in Lagos, approximately £5,200,000 annually. Iwobi is thought to have a net worth of around 11.050 billion, or £22,390,160. Additionally, he is a PUMA brand ambassador. Wilfred Ndidi. Photo: Idris Dawodu for Guardian Life 3. Wilfred Ndidi has a net worth of 12.83 billion yuan, making him the Premier League’s highest-earning African player. One of Leicester City’s most important players is the star midfielder, who is 25. Following his consistent performances for the Nigerian national team, Ndidi has also been the subject of speculation regarding the position of captain of the Super Eagles.
Ndidi is one of the most reserved Super Eagles players and a family man, so he may not be a “showman” when it comes to his wealth or how he spends it. Wilfred Ndidi is thought to have a net worth of about 12.831 billion yen (£26,130,000). He is also a Fanbants brand ambassador. (FILES) In this file photo taken on February 27, 2020 Manchester United’s Nigerian striker Odion Ighalo reacts at the final whistle during the UEFA Europa League round of 32 second leg football match between Manchester United and Club Brugge at Old Trafford in Manchester, north west England, on February 27, 2020. – Manchester United extended Odion Ighalo’s loan spell until January 2021 on June 1, 2020 to ensure the Nigerian striker will be able to finish the 2019/20 season with the Premier League club. (Photo by Oli SCARFF / AFP) 2. Odion Ighalo has a net worth of 14.6 billion yen, making him the Super Eagles star with the second highest net worth and highest salary in the world. The striker, who was born in Lagos, helped his Saudi Arabian team Al-Hilal win the league in the 2021/22 season.
One of Nigeria’s wealthiest athletes is the former Manchester United player, who regularly flaunts his incredible wealth on social media. Ighalo is thought to be worth around 14.608 billion yen (£29,619,200). He is well-known for his charitable work and is one of the Super Eagles’ most popular players. Nigeria’s forward Victor Moses celebrates scoring a penalty to equalise during the Russia 2018 World Cup Group D football match between Nigeria and Argentina at the Saint Petersburg Stadium in Saint Petersburg on June 26, 2018. / AFP PHOTO / Giuseppe CACACE 1. With an estimated net worth of around 17.766 billion (£36,140,000), Spartak Moscow star Victor Moses is the wealthiest Super Eagles player in 2022. One of the Super Eagles’ most successful club players is the former Chelsea player.
The attacker, who was born in Lagos and is 31 years old, is unquestionably a legend for the Super Eagles. In 2013, he helped Nigeria win the Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON).
Moses is the richest Super Eagles player because he has won titles at the highest level of European football with Chelsea in 2017 and Inter Milan in the 2020/21 season, respectively, throughout his career. 